Here you can find the materials for the R Workshop:

Introduction to R Programming.

Scripts:

The workshop is held with Google Colab. Google Colab instantaneously runs Jupyter Notebooks in your browser with an R Kernel.

  • Google Colab Links:

    • Part I (R Basics)
    • Part II (Data Manipulation with the tidyverse)
    • Solutions to the Exercises

If you prefer to use RStudio to run the scripts, you have two options:

  • You can find the raw Rmarkdown files here in this repository. Download them and open them in your local RStudio.

  • Simply start a Binder instance which will create a session of RStudio in your Browser (may take a little bit):

Note: If you are using Binder dont forget to download the files before you close out the session because otherwise anything you added will be lost!

  • If you just want to look a look at the scripts (not interactive) you can check it out here:

    • Part I (R Basics)
    • Part II (Data Manipulation with the tidyverse)
    • Solutions to the Exercises

  • If you prefer the raw Jupyter Notebooks file, you can find them here.
